dialogue: …and that was all before 10 o’clock. The caterer rang and said it was going to be Chicken Kiev instead of Chicken Tarragon. And then the florist phoned to say there aren’t any tulips. Oh, and the chilliest has carpel-tunel syndrome. We’re not gonna be…
Well, up yours too!
Sorry.
How’s it gonna be all right?!
Hello?
We don’t have to.
No. But, Monica and I were talking, and-and I was so upset about the hall being knocked down, and she suggested that we put the wedding off for a bit.
She said, "If I’m not gonna be happy getting married somewhere that we find in a day, well then we should just postpone it."
I realize that people are going to be disappointed. But, I’m sure they’ll come back when we can do it right.
So what are you saying? It’s now or never?
Or?
Monica, why have you brought me here of all places?!
I tell you, this wedding is not going to happen.
Oh God.
It’s perfect.
Ohh, here comes my dad and stepmum. Mister and Misses Geller, this is Steven and Andrea Waltham.
What-what’s going on?!
What was all that about?
I, Emily...
Take thee Ross...
As my lawfully wedded husband, in sickness and in health, until death parts us.
Yes.
Thank goodness.
Really?! Well, that’s just lovely, isn’t it? I must’ve missed your call, even though I didn’t leave the flat all day.

Oh, no-no-no, that’s not rude! It’s perfectly in keeping with a trip that I’ve already been run down by one of your wiener carts, and been strip-searched at John F. Kennedy Airport, apparently to you people, I look like someone who’s got a balloon full of cocaine stuffed up their bum.
Me too.
Ross.
It was dreadful. I felt terrible about how I acted when you said those wonderful things.
Ross umm, there’s something that I’ve got to tell you, there’s-there’s someone else.
I’ve uh, I’ve come to talk to Ross.
What?
I was going to call him, but…
I’d really rather talk to him.
I uh, I’ve been to his apartment and he wasn’t there, and uh. I need to talk to him, so do you have any idea where he is?
Ross, I love you!
My uncle dragged us there. But, it actually it turned out to be really interesting.
No one’s ever thrown me a surprise party before!
You’re so sweet! And I’m so surprised!
Oh, but the party’s only just getting started!
So why did you plan a party at the same time?
But Ross, I’m such having a great time! Your sister has just been telling me that you used to dress up like little, old ladies and hold make-believe tea parties.
I’ll go.
But, we can’t go now. It looks like Rachel’s gonna put on a skit.
I left a bra drying on the shower rod, you don’t think your son will think it’s yours and be horribly traumatised?
Well that’s ambitious.
That’s Carol with your son!
Me too!
Oh, well, I’ll show you around.
Oh, there’s tonnes of terrific stuff—I’ll go with you!
Are you all right?
Hey! I missed you.
Oh, so did I.
Hello everyone. So who am I saying hello too?
She's there?!
Ross, take me off speakerphone.
How can you do this too me?! I thought I'd made my feelings about Rachel perfectly clear!
You obviously can't keep away from her.
I'll feel better when I'm there, and I can know where you are all the time.
You're right.
No.
Ross, I'm only ringing to say stop harassing my relatives. Good-bye!
Really? About what?
I miss you to. Well, at least I think I do.
I understand that would be difficult.
I don't know, it's just…
All right.
I did. Now I'm the idiot.
Ross, there's one thing that really scares me still.
Well, you have to understand how humiliating it was for me up on that altar in front of my entire family, all my friends.
And then after decided to forgive you, seeing you at the airport catching our plane with her.
I mean, I can't-I can't be in the same room as her! It drives me mad just thinking of you being in the same room as her!
All right. I'll come to New York and we'll try and make this work.
Oh, blimey, I still can’t believe you’ve got an earring!
He does that?!
I think it makes you look really dangerous.
I love both of you!
I wish I didn’t have to go.
Ohh, Ross, please!
Don’t do this to me, again. You’d know I’d stay here in a minute, but I’d really miss so much work, they’ll fire me.
I wish I could.
I don’t think you understand packing. Look, I just don’t want to leave it to the last minute. Last time I left in such a rush, I left my knickers here.
You didn’t!
I packed while you were gone. I left some knickers under your pillow.
What?!
Ohh, no. Ugh. Oh, leaving London, my whole family lives there.
My job!
Yeah, but it-it-it’s my whole life—you come to England.
Ohh, I don’t think so. I mean it would be different if it was way into the future –and-and-and we were getting married or something.
Oh no, no, right I shouldn’t have said married. Uh, please don’t go freaky on me. I didn’t mean it. Well, I didn’t say it; I take it back!
Why don’t we what?
You are mad!
We’ve only known each other for six weeks!
My parents are going to be really mad.
Yes.
Yes!
Oh my God!
We’re getting married!
Yes.
Ohh, it’s a bit small.
It was.
Umm, no.
I mean, we know it’s a bit hasty but, uh, it just feels so right, so…
I can’t believe you really walk alone here! I mean, you hear such stories about New York.
So how are you? I’ve been meaning to ring you ever since I arrived but umm, well, I’ve been rather busy.
Oh my God. I think you’re right.
Well I mean, you’re American to start with. You don’t even have rugby here.
I’m just going to say hi to the lads. All right?
Liam, do me a favour. Tell the lads to go easy on Ross, it’s his first time.
I can’t believe they’re doing that to him! I told them to go easy on him!
That’s just halftime, there’s more of this.
Right.
Okay.
Ross, they are killing you out there!
All right, all right, if you insist on doing this, at least let me help you.
No. That’s not what I’m saying. I just may know a few things that might help you inflict some pain.
Yeah? Listen closely, Devon has got a weak ankle.
One swift kick and he’ll back off.
And that big bloke with the beard, he has got a trick hip. Yeah. And uh, and David over there, I heard he doesn’t wear a cup.
And uh, Liam, Liam’s got bad knees. You hit him right and he’ll go down like a lamp.
I don’t care! You just get him!
You were amazing out there.
Oh my God!
You really enjoyed yourself didn’t you?
I think you’ve got concussion.
Yes, yes, do go on.
Just keep smiling.
I hate you!!
So what did he decide? Does your Uncle Nathan get an invite or not?
Yeah, they’re fine.
Really?
I don’t think I’d be comfortable with any of my old lovers there.
Earl Grey?
